<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-03-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-03-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="691" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d691">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">868.248/142</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of the Navy</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Knox</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-29">March 29,
                                    1941</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>For your information, I quote the following message which I received
                                from the President today: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>“Authorized cancellation previous allocation 30 Grumman
                                        planes to British and transfer these planes to Greece.”</p>
                                </quote>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Frank Knox</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>